[MK] case called at 8:53am
Defendant Jose A. Aguirre not in court.  DA Monica Hall ttorney Brookellen Teuber in court for State of Wisconsin. 
DA Hall verifies victim rights compliance.  
This case is scheduled for Preliminary Hearing today, and the State's officer witness is present. 
The Court issues a Bench Warrant-Body only, returnable to any Jefferson County magistrate. 
recess 8:54am
reconvene 9:05am
Defendant Jose A Aguirre now appears.  The Court learns that Mr. Aguirre was present in the courthouse timely for the hearing, but he has been in the lobby area--he did not understand that he was to come into the courtroom. 
The Court vacates the warrant-order. 
Right to counsel is reviewed.  Mr. Aguirre indicates that he works part-time and he wishes to have counsel. The Court requires Mr. Aguirre to telephone the Jefferson Public Defenders Office (telephone number is provided) by 12:00pm today. Further Mr. Aguirre is to go to the Clerk of Courts Office, Room 115, now to complete and file a petition form to request appointment of counsel so that the clerk has the petition to process if it is learned that Mr. Aguirre does not qualify for PD representation. 
recess 9:08am

NEXT:  Status Conference (status of counsel; JA- note in calendar comments that the case is at prelim stage) on September 22nd at 9:00am
State Public Defender Determination of Financial Eligibility - Defendant not eligible.
Scheduling Order
Preliminary hearing on September 8, 2022 at 08:30 am.
